{"ts":"2026-06-27T22:47:33.561Z","type":"agent_event","event":{"type":"content_end","contentType":"reasoning","reasoning":"**Refining CORS and Deployment**\n\nI'm thrilled the tests passed; it's a great sign. Now, I'm diving into the CORS and deployment configurations to ensure Phase 6 finalization compliance. Specifically, I'm checking `backend/app/core/config.py` for any needed adjustments to production CORS settings. I'm also turning my attention to deployment.\n\n\n**Adjusting CORS Configurations**\n\nI've hit a snag. My current CORS settings are not aligned with the production environment variables outlined in the setup guide. Specifically, the guide requires `CORS_ORIGINS` to include `https://portal.gff.ai,https://admin.gff.ai` and `FRONTEND_BASE_URL` should be `https://portal.gff.ai`. I need to ensure these are set correctly in the environment and that the loading from the environment variable will parse a list of strings correctly, and I'm investigating how this is handled within the `get_cors_origins` method.\n\n\n"}}
