(CORS) Issues\n./docs/PHASE_5_MVP_BACKEND.md:*   **Symptom**: The console shows `Access-Control-Allow-Origin` errors, or login handshakes fail with network/CORS block messages.\n./docs/PHASE_5_MVP_BACKEND.md:    1. Check your `backend/.env` file. Ensure `CORS_ORIGINS` is configured with the exact URL of your running frontend (usually `http://localhost:3000`).\n./docs/PHASE_3_INTERACTIVE_TOOLS.md:|   |         - SlowAPI Rate Limiter           - CORS Policy Manager           |  |\n./docs/PHASE_3_INTERACTIVE_TOOLS.md:# --- NETWORKING & CORS CORRIDORS ---\n./README.md:| `CORS_ORIGINS` | `https://portal.gff.ai,https://admin.gff.ai` | Allowed frontend domains (CORS compliance) |\n./public/insights/insight.svg:<image id=\"image0_750_4030\" width=\"4096\" height=\"2234\" preserveAspectRatio=\"none\" xlink:href=\"data:image/jpeg;base64,\n[... output truncated: 27302418 chars total. Refine the command (grep, head, tail) to view the elided middle ...]\nCase 3: Mismatched client_id forbidden\\n230 |     try:\\n231 |         require_client_access(req1, other_client_user)\\n232 |         assert False, \\\"Should raise 403\\\"\\n233 |     except HTTPException as e:\\n234 |         assert e.status_code == 403\\n235 |         assert \\\"Access to this client's data is denied\\\" in e.detail\\n236 |         \\n237 |     # Case 4: client_id in query parameters\\n238 |     req2 = MockRequest(query_params={\\\"client_id\\\": \\\"42\\\"})\\n239 |     assert require_client_access(req2, client_admin_user) == client_admin_user\\n240 |     \\n241 |     # Case 5: Invalid client_id format\\n242 |     req_invalid = MockRequest(path_params={\\\"client_id\\\": \\\"abc\\\"})\\n243 |     try:\\n244 |         require_client_access(req_invalid, client_admin_user)\\n245 |         assert False, \\\"Should raise 400\\\"\\n246 |     except HTTPException as e:\\n247 |         assert e.status_code == 400\\n248 |         assert \\\"Invalid client_id format\\\" in e.detail\\n249 |         \\n250 |     print(